Sentencas: Oxygen electrodes prepared by infiltration of yttria stabilized zirconia backbone with Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.95 barrier layer and LaNi1-xCoxO3-delta (x = 0.4 to 0.7) catalyst for application in reversible solid oxide cells have been studied.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The effect of temperature and Ni:Co ratio on their phase composition, microstructure and electrochemical properties are discussed.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: It was shown that oxygen electrodes infiltrated with LaNi0.5-Co0.5O3.delta had the lowest polarization resistance, i.e. 67 m Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The performance of a fuel electrode supported solid oxide cell with infiltrated oxygen electrode in both fuel cell and electrolysis mode was tested.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical characterization of the solid oxide cell showed that the resistance contribution from these oxygen electrodes to the overall cell resistance is minor i.e. approximately 20 m Omega cm(2) at a temperature of 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The cell was also tested in the steam electrolysis mode at a constant current of -1.0 A cm(-2) at 800 degrees C for 240 h.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The oxygen electrode showed reasonable degradation rate with the oxygen electrode resistance of 33 m Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C after 240 h of testing.
Titulo: High performance LaNi1-xCoxO3-δ (x=0.4 to 0.7) infiltrated oxygen electrodes for reversible solid oxide cells
